    <section class="section" aria-labelledby="research-intro-heading">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="content-width">
          <h2 id="research-intro-heading" class="visually-hidden">Our Research Mission</h2>
          <p class="lead">
            At the Still Me Project, our research mission is grounded in a fundamental conviction: that identity continuity frameworks and rigorous cognitive care methodologies can meaningfully improve the lives of individuals and families affected by memory loss. We pursue evidence-based approaches that bridge the gap between academic inquiry and real-world application.
          </p>
          <p class="lead">
            Our interdisciplinary team collaborates with clinicians, technologists, and family caregivers to develop tools and frameworks that honor the complexity of human identity. Every initiative begins with listening &mdash; to the people most affected &mdash; and proceeds with methodological integrity, ethical grounding, and a commitment to measurable impact.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>


