    <!-- ==========================================
         OUR METHODOLOGY
         ========================================== -->
    <section class="section" aria-labelledby="methodology-heading">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="content-width">
          <div class="section-header">
            <span class="section-label">How We Work</span>
            <h2 id="methodology-heading">Our Methodology</h2>
          </div>
          <p class="lead">
            Our research methodology is human-first, community-informed, and ethically grounded. We begin every initiative by centering the lived experiences of individuals with cognitive change and the families who support them. From there, we apply rigorous qualitative and quantitative methods to develop frameworks that are both scientifically sound and practically meaningful.
          </p>
          <p>
            We believe that responsible innovation requires transparency, accountability, and an unwavering commitment to the dignity of every participant. Our ethical review processes ensure that all research activities meet the highest standards of informed consent, data protection, and community benefit. We publish our findings openly and invite peer review, because the work of identity preservation belongs to everyone.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>


